{"text": ["This is law is rigid; it is only the execution of it that is lax.", "Of course, where there is so much fighting, the students make it a point to keep themselves in constant practice with the foil.", "One often sees them, at the tables in the Castle grounds, using their whips or canes to illustrate some new sword trick which they have heard about; and between the duels, on the day whose history I have been writing, the swords were not always idle; every now and then we heard a succession of the keen hissing sounds which the sword makes when it is being put through its paces in the air, and this informed us that a student was practicing."], "style": "<MT>", "title": "A_TRAMP_ABROAD"}
