{"text": ["And what did the husband do?", "He plucked forth that knife, and kneeling by the body of his lost one, swore to 'consecrate his life to the extermination of all the human scum that bear the hated name of Lynch.'", "That was it.", "He had been hunting down the Lynches and slaughtering them, from that day to this--twenty years."], "style": "<MT>", "title": "Life on the Mississippi"}
