{"text": ["Of this, perhaps, the most remarkable example I can give is the effect produced on nearly every class of readers by the appearance of Captain Basil Hall's 'Travels in North America.'", "In fact, it was a sort of moral earthquake, and the vibration it occasioned through the nerves of the republic, from one corner of the Union to the other, was by no means over when I left the country in July 1831, a couple of years after the shock.", "I was in Cincinnati when these volumes came out, but it was not till July 1830, that I procured a copy of them."], "style": "<MT>", "title": "Life on the Mississippi"}
